All the four wards in Uriri Sub County were represented in the week-long tournament aimed at nurturing talents and empowering youths during the prolonged holidays occasioned by Covid-19.
All participants received assorted prizes with the winners bagging Sh50,000 each, a trophy, two sets of uniform and a ball. In his new year’s message to the country, the President called for a renewal of minds in the New Year 2021. He paraded the newly elected Msambweni MP Feisal Bader as the “firstborn” of the so called Hustler's Movement. Ever since Abiy Ahmed came to power, the Tigray regional government has been at odds with the central government.